.TH BTR-MD 1 "May 2026" "btr-md 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
btr-md \- better markdown desktop editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B btr-md
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B btr-md
opens a Tauri desktop Markdown editor and preview window. It supports live
preview, bundled themes, Mermaid diagrams, and KaTeX math rendering.
.PP
When a single
.I FILE
is supplied, btr-md opens that Markdown file at startup. When multiple
files are supplied, btr-md starts one process for each file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --list-themes
Print available themes to standard output, one per line, as
.I slug
followed by a tab and the display name, then exit.
.TP
.B --open-dialog
Start normally and open the desktop file picker once the window is ready.
This is used by the desktop file action named "Open File...".
.TP
.I FILE
Open a Markdown file. Supported extensions are
.BR .md ,
.BR .markdown ,
.BR .mdown ,
and
.BR .mkd .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/btr-md/themes
User theme directory. When
.I XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset, btr-md uses
.IR ~/.config/btr-md/themes .
.TP
.I /app/share/btr-md/themes
Bundled theme directory used by the Flatpak package.
.TP
.I /usr/share/btr-md/themes
System theme directory used by native packages and AppImage payloads.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xdg-open (1),
.BR flatpak (1)
